&lt;h3&gt;About the Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netlify’s self-serve funnel is the path a developer takes from first deploy to a paying, growing account, and it is one of the largest growth opportunities at Netlify. We are hiring a Principal Product Manager to own that funnel as a product and lead the motion that grows self-serve revenue through the product itself. You will own activation, conversion, in-product expansion, and retention as a single number, and you will shape how we measure and experiment on the funnel as a discipline. This is a foundational role with a clear line to revenue, and you will define and evolve how growth works at Netlify for years. You report into Product and partner across Engineering, Data, Design, GTM, and Finance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Netlify’s self-serve funnel as one product and one number: net-new self-serve ARR, counting new revenue plus expansion minus contraction and churn. Drive all four parts toward our growth goal rather than optimizing one metric at a time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the measurement foundation the funnel runs on. Strengthen attribution, define a top-of-funnel number we trust, and put our product and AI-visibility analytics to work so we can better understand where users come from and where they stall.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stand up an experimentation practice and run it - Ship experiments early, build the team&#39;s experimentation muscle, and shape how we invest in the platform over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Raise activation. Define the early milestones that predict a paying account, measure time-to-value, and shorten the path to a user’s first meaningful outcome on the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow conversion. Own every paid conversion path, understand the drivers behind each one, and focus investment on the highest-impact opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a self-serve expansion motion by creating clear paths for customers to expand usage (credits, seats, add-ons) and defining the signals that indicate an account ready to grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with GTM on the handoff from product-qualified accounts to sales, so the product-led and sales-led motions reinforce each other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the funnel roadmap, articulate the strategy to executives, and develop other PMs as the growth practice grows around you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years in product management, including experience owning a self-serve or PLG funnel end to end for a developer-focused, usage-priced, or consumption-priced product. You have owned a growth system with direct accountability for activation, conversion, expansion, and retention outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growth PM expertise where you have designed experiments, ran a robust experimentation practice, owned business outcomes rather than individual feature areas, and used product analytics to inform decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency with funnel instrumentation: attribution, event taxonomy, cohorting. You can shape and improve measurement yourself, not just consume a dashboard someone else built.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Command of in-product monetization mechanics: paywalls, free-to-paid flows, upgrade and buy-more paths, and credit or usage economics. You experiment around pricing without owning pricing strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A record of driving measurable business outcomes, not just shipping features. You have moved a revenue or retention number and can show the work behind it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional leadership with Data, Design, Engineering, GTM, and Finance, and the credibility to operate alongside executives and shape company-level strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort building in a fast-moving environment where you help define new practices, operating models, and ways of working around a new mandate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nice to have: experience with an AI, agent

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netlify is hiring a Social Media Manager to own Netlify’s company social handles and help anyone creating a website or an app understand what’s possible when they build with AI on Netlify.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re seeking someone who can turn what Netlify ships, teaches, and celebrates into a social presence people who build with AI want to follow. You’ll write, publish, engage, experiment, and measure what works across the channels where developers and vibecoders pay attention. The goal is simple: make Netlify more visible, more useful, and more trusted among people building for the web with AI.&amp;nbsp;This role is for someone who has already managed brand social channels and understands how to earn attention with a variety of audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Netlify’s day-to-day social presence across X, LinkedIn, Bluesky, Discord, and other priority channels. You’ll write, publish, reply, monitor, and engage from the company handles with speed, context, and care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take new features, product launches, change log updates, customer examples, and community activity and turn them into clear, useful posts builders understand and care about.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage the social calendar by maintaining a content calendar that balances launches, education, builder spotlights, community moments, founder content, and timely conversations in the ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the broader builder ecosystem to find, celebrate, and amplify people building with Netlify, especially developers and vibe coders creating with AI tools and agentic workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support community and campaigns and help&amp;nbsp;promote community challenges, contests, launches, events, and builder programs through social content, live engagement, recaps, clips and storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use platform behavior and social algorithms to improve reach, engagement, and defined performance metrics. You’ll track what’s working and understand why. Then use that learning to drive better content, stronger builder engagement, and more product interest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll manage intake, approvals, launch support, calendars, reporting, and AI-assisted workflows, while working with Dev Advocates, Product, and Support so Netlify’s public presence stays engaging, helpful, and timely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience managing social media for a technical, developer, AI, or product-led brand.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing high-volume brand handles, from publishing and engagement to monitoring and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dev-culture fluency and good public judgment. You know what earns trust and what builders take seriously. When threads move fast, you know when to reply accurately, and when to pull in help.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enough technical fluency to understand what Netlify ships and strong writing skills to explain it accurately and make it relevant to various audiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong operating habits across calendars, intake, approvals, launch support, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An experimental, data-aware mindset where you love trying new tools or posting strategies. You can explain the &quot;why&quot; behind the engagement rate and use that data to improve social performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
